German State Will Pursue Nuclear-Free Policy, Handlesblatt Says

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-04-16T13:18:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/german-state-will-pursue-nuclear-free-policy-handlesblatt-says.html
     April 16 (Bloomberg) --The German state of North Rhine-
Westphalia wants to pursue its own “nuclear-free”  energy
policy , Harry Voigtsberger, the state’s finance minister, said
in an interview with Handelsblatt.  The state already has sources of renewable energy and
modern gas and coal-fired plants that can provide stable and
secure power at acceptable prices, he said in the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 